1ln.title: Arbital requisites
1ln.clickbait: To understand some things you often need to understand some other things.
1ln.text:
[summary: A requisite is the unit of knowledge in Arbital. It's most often used when a page [3jf requires] prior understanding of some topic or when a page [3jg teaches] some topic. To see the full list of all requisites you've interacted with, visit [https://arbital.com/requisites/ your requisites page].]

A requisite is the unit of knowledge in Arbital. Any [16x page] can be used as a requisite. When it is, it'll have additional per-user state associated with it: "not known", "known", and "wanted." By default, all new users' requisites are in the "not known" state.

Requisites are most often used when a page [3jf requires] prior understanding of some topic or when a page [3jg teaches] some topic. Arbital uses these connections to create [1rt dynamic paths] that are tailored to each user. As the user goes through the path, they acquire the requisites that each page teaches them.

The "wanted" state is used to track the requisites the user is interested in. Usually this is done by using [1m6 questionnaires]. This allows further [2gy fine-tuning] of the generated path.

To see the full list of all requisites you've interacted with, visit [https://arbital.com/requisites/ your requisites page].
